  "prompt": "Does the ISS have a good WiFi connection?",
  "response": "The International Space Station (ISS) does have internet access, but it's not comparable to typical WiFi connections on Earth. The internet connection on the ISS is provided through a combination of satellite communications and data relay systems. While astronauts can use email and certain internet services, the connection is relatively slow and can be affected by latency and bandwidth limitations. Streaming video or using data-heavy applications are generally not feasible. However, astronauts can use the internet for research, communication, and even personal use during their off-duty time.",
